.TH NEO-AGENTS 1 "March 2026" "neo 0.1.0" "Neo CLI Manual"
.SH NAME
neo-agents \- list available agents (built-in and custom from .neo/agents/)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B neo agents
.RB [ \-\-output
.IR format ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B neo agents
lists all available agents that can be dispatched via
.BR neo-run (1).
This includes both built-in agents from the @neotx/agents package and any custom
agents defined in the project's .neo/agents/ directory.
.PP
The output shows the agent name, model used, sandbox mode, and source location.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-output =\fIformat\fR
Output format. Use
.B json
for machine-readable JSON output.
.SH OUTPUT COLUMNS
.TP
.B NAME
The agent identifier used when dispatching via
.BR neo-run (1).
.TP
.B MODEL
The AI model the agent uses (e.g., claude-3-opus, claude-3-sonnet).
.TP
.B SANDBOX
Whether the agent runs in sandbox mode (read-only) or has write access.
.TP
.B SOURCE
Location of the agent definition (built-in or custom path).
.SH FILES
.TP
.B .neo/agents/
Project-local custom agent definitions directory. Agents here override built-in
agents with the same name.
.SH EXAMPLES
List all available agents:
.PP
.RS
.nf
neo agents
.fi
.RE
.PP
Output as JSON:
.PP
.RS
.nf
neo agents --output json
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Agent definitions not found (is @neotx/agents installed?).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR neo (1),
.BR neo-run (1)
